# Vault vs MCP Server Separation

## Context

When adding new intelligence data to Salvador ecosystem

## Pattern

Salvador has clear separation: the VAULT (salvador) contains intelligence data (JSON, YAML), while the MCP SERVER (salvador-mcp) provides the API. Updates require changes to both.

## Example

```typescript
// Step 1: Add data to vault
// /salvador/intelligence/data/workflow-patterns.json
{
  "masterStoryProtocol": { ... }
}

// Step 2: Update MCP tool to expose it
// /salvador-mcp/src/tools/get-storybook-patterns.ts
pattern: z.enum([..., 'masterStoryProtocol', 'all'])

// Step 3: Rebuild MCP & reload intelligence
npm run build
salvador_reload_intelligence()
```

## Why

Vault is the source of truth for design system knowledge. MCP is the access layer. This separation allows updating intelligence without changing server code, and vice versa.
